Justification: The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. Here, the claim is "Eliana works tirelessly." The P-type arguments all rely on the assumption that Eliana does not achieve lasting results, which is derived from other premises. However, the S-type arguments show that achieving lasting results is possible, which would satisfy the dedicated environmentalist condition without requiring tireless work. Since there is a minimal semantic basis (e.g., achieving lasting results) that is not contained in any P-type argument's justification—because the P arguments assume no lasting results—C11 is not satisfied.